** Software Engineer **

As part of ARN, the recognised leader in audio in Australia, you have an
opportunity to share your voice on the future of audio. Audio is booming and
we are defining it. We are entertainers. ** We create moments that ** move **
people, and that people ** move to ** . ** We are investing in audio’s
smartest advertising, experts, and innovations. This gives us unparalleled
understanding of our audience and the content that moves them and helps us
form ** quality connections ** with our customers. It’s our commitment to
creating moments that move people that makes us memorable. ​

  

As a ** Software Engineer, ** you will have the opportunity to join an awesome
team and collaborate on exciting projects which enhance the digital
experiences of our people and customers. If you have a background as a full
stack developer or engineer and want to extend your career to new heights,
this will be a role that will allow you to grow and become the very best you
can be.

  

Reporting to the Engineering Director you will have a passion for building
real solutions, a drive to work with exciting technology such as AI and
possess an eye for detail and not be afraid to continually share your ideas
with the team. You will currently be a junior to mid-level developer who
thrives on challenges and is serious about building a future around
technology.

** This position can be based in Sydney or Brisbane. **

  

** About the Role: **

  * Develop and deliver software features. 
  * Ensure team standards are met and processes are followed. 
  * Work with the team to prioritise features and estimate time/complexity. 
  * Proactively identify areas where existing software, standards or processes could be improved. 
  * Provide level 3 support for custom developed software. 
  * Create fit for purpose documentation. 
  * Proactively share software engineering knowledge and expertise with others. 
  * Be approachable, collaborative, and proactive. 
  * Be constantly learning and educating those around you. 
  * Advocate for high quality and continuous improvement of people, process and technology. 

  

** What you'll have: **

  * Prior experience in a Software Engineering or Full Stack Developer style role. 
  * Experience testing solutions developed by team members and a willingness to thoroughly test and provide feedback. 
  * Experience implementing secure coding techniques. 
  * Radio/media/broadcasting industry experience – high advantageous! 
  * Security based software principles, including privacy best practises. 
  * Strong understanding of Agile development methodologies. 
  * User experience best practises and a knowledge of WCAG. 
  * Engineering best practices including Agile methodologies and version control. 
  * Excellent skills in at least two development languages. 
  * Experience with Microsoft .NET Core (C# and Blazor). 
  * Technologies such as Azure DevOps, SQL Server and Entity Framework. 
  * Working with hybrid solutions (On-Premise and Cloud). 

** What’s in it for you! **

  

  * ARNSocial Work Perks which can include – various giveaway & events, FREE and discounted tickets. 
  * Novated Leasing + Super Salary Sacrifice | Paid Birthdays off |Paid Parental Leave | Charity Leave. 
  * Discounts on lifestyle, entertainment with big name brands including Health fund discounts. 
  * Education Assistance | Career Development with consistent quality training | Long term career progression. 

** Our Culture: ** We have four behaviours that make up our "Culture in Action" which describe how we act every day to create a great place to work: 

  

  * ** Aim High ** ** ​ ** \- Set big goals and achieve together. 
  * ** Own It ** ​ – Take ownership and be solutions focused. 
  * ** Be Your Best Self ** ​ - Create the environment we need to thrive. 
  * ** Make a Difference ** ​ – Seek out ways to have a positive impact. 

